Question 4
How do you implement error boundaries using errorCallback?
Companies that asked this: Salesforce, IBM, TCS, Accenture, Microsoft

Answer:
errorCallback is LWC's error boundary mechanism that catches JavaScript errors in a component and its children. It prevents errors from crashing the entire application and allows for graceful error handling.

Key Features:

Catches errors in child components - Acts as an error boundary

Provides error details - Error object and stack trace

Allows graceful recovery - Show fallback UI instead of broken component

Logs errors - Can report to error tracking services

Doesn't catch all errors - Only certain types of JavaScript errors

Limitations â€“ Does not catch errors in:

Asynchronous code (e.g. setTimeout, fetch)

Event handlers

The component itself (only its children)

Example: Parent Component Using errorCallback()

parentComponent.js

import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';
 
export default class ParentComponent extends LightningElement {
    hasError = false;
 
    errorCallback(error, stack) {
        console.error('Error caught in parent:', error);
        console.error('Stack trace:', stack);
        this.hasError = true;
    }
}


parentComponent.html

<template>
    <template if:true={hasError}>
        <div class="error">Something went wrong. Please try again later.</div>
    </template>
    <template if:false={hasError}>
        <c-child-component></c-child-component>
    </template>
</template>
Example: Child Component Throwing an Error

childComponent.js

import { LightningElement } from 'lwc';
 
export default class ChildComponent extends LightningElement {
    connectedCallback() {
        // Simulating an error
        throw new Error('Simulated error in child');
    }
}

ðŸ’¡ Interview Tips:

Explain error boundary concept - Catches errors in child components

Show graceful degradation - Fallback UI instead of broken component

Mention what's NOT caught - Async errors, event handlers, timers

Emphasize user experience - Friendly messages and recovery options
